<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="86735" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">Description</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="86735" type="diagnosis and remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">Diagnosis and remarks</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">
The report of this species is a new distribution record to Wuyi Mountains. Head brown, slightly wider than pronotum; compound eyes dark brown; antennae and mouth-parts brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F8002496" captionText="Figure 9. Rhopalopsole flata Yang &amp; Yang, 1995. A Male head and pronotum, dorsal view; B Male terminalia, dorsal view; C Male terminalia, lateral view; D Male terminalia, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e86735.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/711853" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">9</figureCitation>
A). This species can be easily distinguished by the epiproct almost as wide as the central plate of tergum 10 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F8002496" captionText="Figure 9. Rhopalopsole flata Yang &amp; Yang, 1995. A Male head and pronotum, dorsal view; B Male terminalia, dorsal view; C Male terminalia, lateral view; D Male terminalia, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e86735.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/711853" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">9</figureCitation>
B). However, the hind margin of tergum 9 strongly sclerotized (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F8002496" captionText="Figure 9. Rhopalopsole flata Yang &amp; Yang, 1995. A Male head and pronotum, dorsal view; B Male terminalia, dorsal view; C Male terminalia, lateral view; D Male terminalia, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e86735.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/711853" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">9</figureCitation>
B), this characteristic is not consistent with original descriptions; we think this variation should be the interspecific difference.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
